#include <iostream>
#include "Sales_item.h"
  
-Headers from the standard library are enclosed in angle brackets (< >). 
 Those that are not part of the library are enclosed in double quotes (" ").

-File Redirection
$ addItems < infile > outfile
our addition program has been compiled into an executable file addItems(on UNIX systems), 
this command will read transactions from a file named infile and write its output to 
a file named outfile in the current directory.

- We call a function using the call operator (the () operator)